The Future Female Leader Award is a prestigious recognition that celebrates women who demonstrate outstanding leadership potential and contribute to the advancement of gender diversity in business. IESE Business School awarded the Future Female Leader Award to Chinemerem Mezie-Osuocha as the first Nigerian recipient. This year, 42 women from 20 countries for the diverse talents and contributions to the business world, showcasing the success stories of women in traditionally male-dominated industries were reflected upon as a means to inspire other women to pursue their ambitions and break down barriers.
<img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-2020995 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Meme-Reel-2-478x598.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="1600" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Meme-Reel-2-478x598.jpg 478w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Meme-Reel-2-922x1152.jpg 922w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Meme-Reel-2-1229x1536.jpg 1229w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Meme-Reel-2-192x240.jpg 192w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Meme-Reel-2-384x480.jpg 384w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Meme-Reel-2-480x600.jpg 480w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Meme-Reel-2.jpg 1440w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" />
Another of this year’s recipients is Meme Osuocha, a media, marketing, and tech professional from Nigeria and one of the four African women to receive the Future-Female Award. Her dedication to promoting gender diversity in the business world and her commitment to improving the perception of Africans through positive storytelling has made a significant impact, inspiring others to follow in her footsteps.
Her passion for media, technology, people, culture, and marketing, combined with her commitment to support the growth of African businesses makes her a valuable asset to the continent and a worthy recipient for the Future Female Leader Award. Nigerian woman shine brightly on a global stage with the goal of driving progress towards greater gender inclusion in the business world. On receiving the award, Miss Meme said “I strongly believe that gender equity is not just a moral imperative but also a smart business strategy. As a woman who has worked in media, marketing, and tech for many years, I have seen firsthand the positive impact women can have on businesses, communities, and economies when empowered to succeed. When women are given the tools and resources to thrive, businesses thrive, communities prosper, and economies grow. That is why I will continue to advocate for women and play my part in ensuring we continue to work towards gender equity in all aspects of society.” 